Subject: [PATCH] malloc: tcache + unsorted-bin micro-optimisations for gaming

  * tcache_get_n(): fold ternary; prefetch next chunk to hide L2 latency
    on burst allocs.
  * _int_malloc(): prefetch bck in unsorted-bin walk; critical when a
    game frame teardown floods the bin with thousands of chunks.
  * _int_free_chunk(): prefetch nextchunk (and prevchunk when present)
    before acquiring av->mutex, overlapping lock contention with the
    hardware memory fetch.
  * large_csize2tidx(): defense-in-depth bounds clamp.

Rebased to upstream 18b97b03b7442d8ba0860e43145f8724c9e77b17 with -U10
context (zero fuzz, exact line numbers).

